The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also presents a statistical study, which involves modeling the input signal as an i.i.d. process, and investigates the fundamental tradeoff between measurement rate and reconstruction fidelity, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM).
